5:
Magia Fest was great fun! A lot of
things happened, but all's well that
ends well.
9:
That one catchphrase was lovely.
"Dream together"... Inaho is
wonderful, isn't she?
12:
Perhaps the people of Mirea should
adopt a similar catchphrase!
16:
So you're gonna copy th—
You know what, never mind. Toria,
are you feeling all right physically?
19:
I heard that the Liam's magic can
have some nasty side effects...
23:
No problems here!
The food and sweets have been
lovely today, haven't they?
27:
Heh-heh, there is no need to be
surprised! The people of Mirea are a
hardy folk.
30:
We are careful to get 8 hours of
sleep and have a snack at 3 o'clock!
Most importantly, a shared love of
Mirea nurtures a healthy body and
mind!
40:
People from Mirea really love their
country.
44:
Of course! And that bond remains
strong regardless of whether one
remains in Mirea or leaves.
47:
I hope my people are doing well...
Even if they never return to Mirea, all
that matters is their good health...
53:
Wait, you... There's no mistaking it.
You're—
58:
Marfer! The second son of that
farmer in the south of Mirea!
66:
P-Princess Toria! Wh-why are you in
Palpebra?
69:
It has been ages, Marfer! Anyway,
would you please come back to
Mirea?!
78:
I have no choice! If I don't take
action now, Mirea will soon go from
"minimalist" to "petite"!
81:
Marfer, please! Come back to Mirea
as soon as possible, I beg of you!
95:
P-please, tell me why you left! Did
you have a fight with your family? Or
perhaps you were struggling at your
job?
100:
With the way things are in Mirea... I
just can't see myself living there
anymore!
106:
Well... Even the smallest rumor can
spread around the whole country.
And the relatives are always getting
together for parties around New
Year's, and stuff like that!
108:
Everyone wants to go to barbecues
on their days off! If I turn anybody
down because I want the day to
myself, everyone starts worrying
about me!
115:
Wh-where's the problem? They just
invited you because they imagined
you'd be lonely if they didn't!
118:
It was just too much for me! That's
why I came out to Palpebra...
126: I don't understand you at all!
136:
Stay CALM?! How can I stay calm in
the presence of this
INSURRECTIONIST?!
139:
He's clearly been enticed by the fun
of Palpebra! We must find a way to
bring him back to his senses—
145:
Y-you... You're Shero, a hunter who
lived in the west of Mirea! And you...
Celsus! The salesman who lived in
the north!
148:
Your timing is impeccable. Help me
convince Marfer to return to Mirea!
151:
Go on, tell him! Mirea is a finer place
to live, by far! In fact, all three of you
can return together!
158:
Et tu, Celsus?
I know this place is fun! But... surely it
doesn't compare to glorious Mirea!
161:
Oh, uh... That's not quite the issue.
We just don't really fit in back in
Mirea, you know?
163:
Yeah, I think a lot of people were
feeling that, and that's why they left.
Mirea is more like... a place where a
princess would wanna live, or
something?
166: Uh... I can't keep up with this...
174:
B-but, Princess! We love YOU! We
were really worried when we heard
those rumors about the Magia Fest!
176:
Y-yes! I-I'm sorry I can't share your
enthusiasm for Mirea, Princess!
179:
You... can't...
But why? We all hail from Mirea... Do
we not share our hopes and dreams?
183:
O-oh, that's right! How about we
have a barbecue to commemorate
our reunion? Not every week, but it
couldn't hurt to hold just one...
191:
Mark my words—our shared love of
Mirea will not be dismantled so
easily!
194:
One day, we will all share the same
dream once more!
204:
I am relieved to see you three in
such good health. Don't forget to get
your eight hours of sleep and your
three o'clock snack.
208:
And tomorrow we'll have our
barbecue! I'll go shopping
immediately!
212: Do you three like Toria, too?
215:
O-of course! No one in the world is
more lovely than she!
217:
I guess we just feel that it'd be better
if we loved her from a distance, all of
us doing our own thing, or—
223:
...And wasn't that outfit incredible?
Man! Why didn't I think to take a
photo with her?!
226:
...I guess people from Mirea tend to
be on the energetic side.
231:
Hurry up, everyone! We won't get to
eat like pigs if we don't get ready for
tomorrow!
